<Author>SusanofBoston
<Content>Not keeping up with the times Poor hotel for the price. Great location! But other features are far below par.Tiny restaurant /bar combination. Who can enjoy a meal with people on either side of you smoking like chimneys?YIKES.Wireless Internet is a mess. FIrst, a whopping 17E per day! This is disgraceful. It is so easy for any Hotel to install their own system and graciously offer free access. These guys require that you access a 3rd party system, with high security user names and passwords... as if the internet had been invented yesterday and everyone was really afraid of it. Moreover, the only way to get access is to go downstairs, buy a card and scratch off the hidden numbers. The rooms were very small and accoutrements gimicky. Instead of chocolates. the turndown service offers sweets that look like fried eggs. I kid you not. This place is trying to be cool and avant-garde. But they are stuck in the 1990s so it feels silly. Complementary bath salts for two? lovely ...but not when they are charging 17E for something as basic as wireless internet and forcing people to go down to the lobby and buy a card and scratch off the hidden number....Service generally warm and friendly. However, though I wouldn't normally expect anyone to speak English... at a Hotel in City Center at 330E per night, it seems reasonable. I don't deduct anything for this however. There are enough other reasons to rate this hotel a pass. 
