<Author>Wick56
<Content>Great little luxury hotel I am writing this review from the terrace off of our room with a view of Calle San Jeronimo over to the Ritz Carlton. Wanted to write this while it was fresh in my mind. So here goes:First, the soundproofing issue I read about before I booked our room. The rooms are in fact soundproofed for sounds emanating outside of the hotel so when the windows/terrace doors are shut, you can hardly hear any street sounds. You can hear *some* internal sounds, but nothing on the level that I read about prior to staying here...and this after staying up all night due to jet lag. In short, don't get freaked out about the reviews indicating that the hotel is super noisy; it isn't. With that said, we booked a suite on the top floor, so this could be an issue with the rooms on the lower floors, but again, noise just wasn't an issue here. Now with that out of the way, this hotel is great! As stated above, we booked a suite, and it is wonderful, with a huge terrace providing great views. On our first night, our room overlooked the back of the hotel and that wasn't so great, but management moved us to the front of the hotel the very next night and we were very pleased with that. Rooms are clean, spacious and comfortable and the hotel staff is pleasant and helpful. Location is great; just a short walk to the Prado and Puerto de Sol and the many, many colorful tapas bars that dot the area landscape. Added bonus--as a guest of Hotel Villa Real, you have access to the pool/terrace area of Hotel Urban (which is super chic and modern hotel that is literally right around the corner) so if you want to save a buck (or euro, that is), stay at Villa Real and then camp by the pool at Hotel Urban (if that's your thing). You can even charge your poolside your drinks at Hotel Urban to your room at Villa Real! In short, this is a great little luxury hotel. 
