<Author>marleydog
<Content>Excellent Location Spent three nights at the Hotel Villa Real at the end of October, 2006. Booked a standard room through the hotel's website and paid roughly 135 Euro per night. This did not include breakfast. The hotel was prompt in answering an email before we arrived with questions about their service. Taxi to and from Terminal 4 at Barajos Airport cost about 20 Euro per trip and was fast and easy, despite arriving Saturday afternoon.Room was of adequate size, and the two levels as shown in some of the review photographs made it feel more roomy. Bathroom was of a good size, had a full bath with an excellent shower, bidet and two sinks. Toiletries were copious and of good quality. Even included mouthwash. Towels were also good quality. Plenty of storage space and hangers, although one of the built-in closets was a little difficult to access as it was close to the nightstand. Not a big deal. Reading lights on each side of the comfortable king size bed - very important. Decor was an interesting combination of old-fashioned panelling, tiling etc. and sleek modernity.Did not have breakfast in the hotel as there were plenty of bars, cafes around where we could have coffee and croissant or churros for 4 Euros total. The only food I had at the hotel was a plate of calamari with a great tomato and onion sauce in the bar one evening. That was very good, as was the ambience and service in the bar. Small, but attractive, with always plenty of black clad bartenders around with just the right combination of good service and cool attitude.Location was excellent as we were in walking distance of the Prado, the Thyssen, the Reina Sofia and even the Palacio Real and Cathedral. I was able to run in the Retiro Park a couple of times (at a slow 10 minute mile pace a circuit takes about 30 minutes).There seems to be construction on every second street and every fifth building in central Madrid these days so there was some noise early in the morning, and of course life in Madrid goes on late at night - if you want peace and quiet this is not for you.Not a luxurious hotel, but very comfortable and pleasant. We would definitely stay here again. 
