<Content>If cleanliness and quiet are priorities, don't stay here First the good part:location is very convenient especially if you plan to spend some time in the museums. there was a decent amount of space for a junior suite.But the negatives:*the living room part of my suite was infested with ants and other unidentifiable bugs! yuck! *the rug under the coffee table in the living room looked like it has never been cleaned or washed or even vacuumed in a while. this area seems to be the nesting ground of the clony of ants and other bugs.*despite the fact that my room was in a corner on the top floor i heard various plumbing related noise such as the toilet flushing. there is also considerable street noise as well...there are no soundproofed windows that seem to be fairly common at hotels in the center. from the living room, I was also able to hear other guests talking from time to time.*decor of the room could definitely use some spiffing up; it麓s too bad because the genuine ancient mosaic pics on the walls look quite out of place from the cheap nouveau riche furniture. the bathroom looks especially tired...the bathtub has aquired a yellowish patina.*finally, i was quite offended when asked to sign a credit card receipt for the intended duration of my stay on the very evening of the day that i checked in...this is irregular...i have never been asked such a thing and i travel all the time! I do not have any credit issues! what if i decide to cut my stay short? will they credit my charge card for the difference?i booked a junior suite mainly because i felt the rate I was offered on the phone --190 euros--was a fairly good value for its supposed class, location and size of the room. However, the slipshod construction (thin walls, poor paint job) combined with makeshift decor/design make it clear that quality is not a priority here. Poor housekeeping is simply not permissible. This hotel definitely has not aged well despite the fact that it is only a few years old since the gut renovation took place. 
