<Content>OUTSTANDING LOCATION Stayed in Madrid 3 nights. Two nights were on an AMEX certificate and the third night paid for by me at a rate of 125 euro. Staff were exceptionally friendly and helpful at selecting locations, restaurants and recommending activities (flamenco at one of the best tablaos in Madrid). It is not even half a block from the Westin Palace. Walking distance to metro stops and all major sights (less than two blocks from Thyssen Bournemisza and about two or three blocks from the Prado and four blocks from the parque del retiro). Plaza Santa Ana (great for sitting, tapas, and people watching) is around the corner, Gran Via is a few blocks away and Plaza del Sol is in its backyard. In short a great property. As to the room, it was nice with a stepdown sitting area. The bathroom was very nice and the shower / water pressure was amazing!!! I didn't realize how important water pressure was but it was so strong. The robes, turndown service, chocolates and other nice touches that other reviews provide were all there, including a welcome plate of fresh fruit. My wife and I prefer more 'simple' / 'sleeker' hotels such as the W chain and places like Capo d'Africa in Rome, but as I was on an AMEX certificate I didn't have much choice. The Villa Real has a sister property around the corner (the Hotel Urbano) which fits this bill. It is brand new with great bars and a terraced rooftop bar. Also, the Villa Real does not have a pool but the Urbano does which guests at the Villa Real have access to. Great, great hotel at a fraction of the cost of the Westin Palace. The only reason I don't give it an 'excellent' is that the hotel, in general, is not to our taste (decor, bedding, etc.). But in spite of this, i'd stay here again. 
