<Content>Top Notch  Great Location!!! We went to Madrid to see our daughter that is going to school in Alcala. Found the Villa Real on line and appreciated the reviews I had read so decided to make sure and give my input too upon our return. We went over the Easter spring break (April 3-10). This is Holy week in Spain. Lots of processions in the streets. Ended up seeing some of them right from our balcony in the street below our hotel. Amazing! Also this is definitely a top notch hotel. The rooms are extremely clean. Mahogany woodwork throughout, marbel floor/tiles in bathroom, comfortable beds, leather couch in sitting area, complimentary wine, slippers and robe, turn down for beds each night. The location can't be beat, within walking distance to many attractions and plazas. Just blocks from the Prado and Thyssen musuems, close to Retiro park (beautiful), close to Atoche train station (a must if going to other towns for the day/days). Always felt safe and enjoyed the night life. Everyone comes alive at about 8:00 pm and goes to the plazas to eat, shop, and see the sights. The Hotel will get you a taxi (if needed) within minutes. All staff are very accomodating and take great care of you. The bar was nice, the restaurant fabulous (not even that expensive). All in all a terrific place to stay and will definitely recommend to anyone thinking of heading to Madrid. Can't be beat!!! Great Prices too. Miss it already.  
